            <biogHist>
                <p>Hugh was born to Hugh Carmichael, dyke builder, and Mary Carmichael n√©e MacDonald
                    presumably in 1785 given that his baptism took place on 29 March of that year.
                    In 1805 he married Margaret (Peggy) MacNiven and there are two children recorded
                    as living with them in later censuses Mary (b. 1811) and Duncan, tailor (b.
                    1831). </p>
                <p>Hugh died in 1866 at the age of 82 and the probable cause of death noted was
                    disease of the heart.</p>
                <p>Carmichael met with Hugh in 1864 and recorded an account of 'Clann 'Ic
                    Illemhicheil' [Carmichaels] in which he describes the family as being the oldest
                    clan in the area.</p>
